description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you have experience working with data and have competent IT skills? The Information Team are looking for someone to join their innovative team as a Senior Developer. The Information Team have developed a reputation for putting Information in the hands of those who need it, and the role of data has never been so prominent in meeting the complex challenges of modern healthcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for the smooth-running of high-profile projects, as well as developing dynamic tools for clinical and operational staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll identify gaps in our information provision and work to develop solutions to enable evidence-based decision making. From walking patient pathways to understand flows, to working on improvement projects alongside clinical staff, you&#39;ll solve problems and communicate these findings clearly to the organisation through a variety of different platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Providing insight to these problems will need:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;good communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;strong technical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the ability to analyse and challenge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;problem solving&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Richard Ewins, Head of Information Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address:richard.ewins@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
